1
00:00:01,080 --> 00:00:03,520
(UPBEAT INSTRUMENTAL
MUSIC PLAYING ON PA)

2
00:00:22,160 --> 00:00:24,480
(WOMEN SPEAKING OVER RADIO, INDISTINCT)

3
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:26,400
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

4
00:00:29,040 --> 00:00:30,040
(GROWLING SOFTLY)

5
00:00:39,480 --> 00:00:40,600
(HYSTERICAL LAUGHTER ECHOES)

6
00:00:40,680 --> 00:00:44,880
My name is Lucy Hayward
and I'm the last one left.

7
00:00:49,240 --> 00:00:50,520
(MANIACAL LAUGHTER)

8
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:57,200
It's funny. You don't know what's going
to be in your room until you see |It.

9
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,880
Then you realise it could never
have been anything else.

10
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,840
(WATER RUNNING)

11
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:17,200
(ROARING)

12
00:01:18,040 --> 00:01:19,040
(SCREAMING)

13
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:21,440
(GROWLING)

14
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:26,720
The gaps between my worship
are getting shorter.

15
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,800
This is what happened to the others.

16
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,040
(MONSTER GROWLING)

17
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:32,680
-Praise him.
-MALE VOICE: (WHISPERING) Praise him.

18
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:39,360
LUCY: It's all so clear now.
I'm so happy. Praise him.

19
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:41,320
Praise him.

20
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:43,000
(HEAVY BREATHING)

21
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:45,400
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

22
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:51,280
(MONSTER GROWLING)

23
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:56,560
Praise him.

24
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:57,840
MALE VOICE: Praise him.

25
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,080
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

26
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:06,800
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

27
00:02:43,760 --> 00:02:47,520
"Let's go to Ravenscala,” he says.
"The people are 600 feet tall,

28
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:49,200
"you have to talk to them
in hot-air balloons,

29
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:52,760
"and the tourist information centre is
made of one of their hats," he says.

30
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:55,240
I'm sorry, but I don't
see any huge hats.

31
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:58,480
Amy, Beaky, this could be the most
exciting thing I have ever seen.

32
00:02:58,560 --> 00:02:59,640
You're kidding.

33
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:03,360
How could he be excited about a
rubbish hotel on a rubbish bit of Earth?

34
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:06,720
Because, oh simple Pond,
this is not Earth.

35
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,680
This has just been made to
look like Earth.

36
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:11,880
The craftsmanship involved.
Can you imagine?

37
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,400
AMY: What? Then where are we?

38
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:16,800
I don't know. Something must have
yanked us off course.

39
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:18,880
Look at that detail on that
cheese plant.

40
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:19,960
(INHALES DEEPLY)

41
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:22,880
RORY: Right, but who would
mock up an Earth hotel?

42
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:25,200
Colonists, maybe.
Recreating a bit of home.

43
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:28,680
Like when ex-pats open
English pubs in Mallorca.

44
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:30,760
No,

45
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:34,400
whoever did this,
I'm shaking his/her hand/tentacle.

46
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:38,200
Have you seen these?
Look at the labels underneath.

47
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:41,880
"Commander Halke. Defeat."

48
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:44,760
"Tim Heath. Having his photo taken."”

49
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:49,720
"Lady Silvertier. Daleks."

50
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:52,200
"Bruce Barnes. Other people's socks."

51
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:54,160
"Tim Nelson. Balloons."

52
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:56,360
"Nevis Prion. Sabre wolves."

53
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,880
"Royston Le Gould. Plymouth."

54
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:03,520
"Lucy Hayward.

55
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:06,720
"That brutal gorilla.”
Doctor, what does it mean?

56
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:10,960
I don't know, let's find out.

57
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:13,320
(SCREAMING)

58
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,440
-Whoa!
-Well, that was quick.

59
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:16,280
-We surrender!
-No, it's okay, we're not...

60
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:17,440
-We surrender.
-We're nice!

61
00:04:17,520 --> 00:04:18,520
She's threatening me with a chair leg.

62
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,640
-Who are you?
-Oh God, we're back in reception.

63
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:21,960
-We surrender!
-I've never been threatened

64
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,960
with a chair leg before.
No, hang on, I tell a lie.

65
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:26,080
Did you just say,
"It's okay, we're nice"?

66
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:28,840
Okay, I need everyone to shut up now!

67
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,440
Uh, Rita, be careful, yeah?

68
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:33,560
Their pupils are dilated.
They are as surprised as we are.

69
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:36,880
Besides which, if it's a trick,
it'll tell us something.

70
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,480
Oh, you're good.

71
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:40,000
Oh, she's good.

72
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:42,600
Amy, with regret, you're fired.

73
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:44,440
-What?
-I'm kidding.

74
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:45,520
(MOUTHING) We'll talk.

75
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:48,560
I take it from the pathological
compulsion to surrender

76
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:49,760
you're from Tivoli?

77
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:51,920
Yes, the most invaded
planet in the galaxy.

78
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:55,560
Our anthem is called
Glory To "Insert Name Here".

79
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:58,800
You with the face,
Howie, you said you were surprised

80
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:00,040
to be back in reception.

81
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,840
The walls move, everything changes.

82
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:04,280
You, clever one,
what's he talking about?

83
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:07,720
The corridors twist and stretch.
Rooms vanish and pop up somewhere else.

84
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,360
-(CHEERFUL INSTRUMENTAL PLAYING)
-It's like the hotel's alive.

85
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:11,840
-(MUSIC CLICKS OFF)
-That's quite enough of that.

86
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,080
Yeah, and it's huge.

87
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:16,240
-With, like, no way out.
-Have you tried the front door?

88
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:18,920
No, in two days it never occurred
to us to try the front door.

89
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:20,240
Thank God you're here.

90
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,320
(LAUGHING)

91
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:25,480
They're not doors, they're walls.
Walls that look like doors.

92
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:28,320
Doorwalls, if you like, or dwalls.
Wdoors, even.

93
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:30,440
Though you probably got it
when you said they're not doors.

94
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:34,800
I mean, the windows are...
Right, big day for a fan of walls.

95
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:38,680
It's not just that. The rooms have...
things in them.

96
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:41,680
Things? Hello! What kind of things?
Interesting things?

97
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:43,840
I love things. Ask anyone.

98
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:46,160
Bad dreams.

99
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,400
Well, that killed the mood.

100
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,200
How did you get here?

101
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:55,760
I don't know. I just started my shift.
I must have passed out,

102
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:57,000
because suddenly I was here.

103
00:05:58,040 --> 00:06:00,720
Look, I was, er, blogging,
next thing this.

104
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,600
Oh, well, I was at work,
I'm in town planning.

105
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,560
We're lining all the highways with trees

106
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:07,960
so invading forces
can march in the shade.

107
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:09,160
-DOCTOR: Oh.
-Which is nice for them.

108
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,280
DOCTOR: Yeah.

109
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:12,680
So what have we got?
People being snatched from their lives

110
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:15,360
and dropped into an endless shifting
maze that looks like a 1980s hotel

111
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:17,280
with bad dreams in the bedrooms.

112
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,640
Apart from anything else,
that's just rude.

113
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:25,720
We'll pop back to the Tardis,
I'll do a planet-wide diagnostic sweep,

114
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,960
then we'll have a sing-song.

115
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:30,320
Where's the Tardis?
You parked it there, didn't you?

116
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:32,000
What's a Tardis?

117
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:34,480
Our way out. And it's gone.

118
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:35,840
(TAPE BEGINS PLAYING)

119
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:37,280
(UPBEAT INSTRUMENTAL
MUSIC PLAYING ON PA)

120
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:41,200
Okay.

121
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:43,600
This is bad. At the moment,
I don't know how bad

122
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:47,400
but certainly we're three buses, a long
walk and eight quid in a taxi from good.

123
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Are there any more of you?

124
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:54,800
Joe, but he's, uh, tied up right now.

125
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:56,640
Doing what?

126
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:59,720
No, I mean, he's tied up right now.

127
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,320
(ALL LAUGHING)

128
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:08,600
(INAUDIBLE)

129
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,320
(WOOD CREAKS, LAUGHTER STOPS)

130
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,040
Hello.

131
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,520
I'm the Doctor.

132
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:30,160
We're going to die here.

133
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,960
Well, they certainly didn't
mention that in the brochure.

134
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:34,480
Is Joe there? Can I have a quick word?

135
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:36,800
Oh, it's still me, Doctor.
But I've seen the light.

136
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:40,280
I lived a blasphemous life
but he has forgiven my inconstancy

137
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:43,240
and soon, he shall feast.

138
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,680
Well, you've been here for two days,
what's he waiting for?

139
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:47,440
We weren't ready.

140
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,240
We were still raw.

141
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,840
But now you're what?

142
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:53,960
-Cooked?
-If you like.

143
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:56,880
Soon you will be, too.

144
00:07:57,280 --> 00:08:01,120
Be patient. First, find your room.

145
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,800
My room?

146
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:06,960
There's a room here
for everyone, Doctor.

147
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,560
Even you.

148
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:17,280
-You said you'd seen the light now.
-Nothing else matters any more.

149
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,680
Only him.

150
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:26,160
It's like these things. I used to hate
them. They make me laugh now.

151
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:29,120
(LAUGHS HYSTERICALLY)

152
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:33,520
Gottle o' geer, gottle o' geer!

153
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:35,640
(ALL LAUGHING)

154
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,480
You should go.

155
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:47,680
He'll be here soon.

156
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,040
I think you should come with me.

157
00:08:57,920 --> 00:08:59,640
(MUSIC PLAYING ON PA)

158
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:03,320
Why you four?

159
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,000
That's what I don't understand.

160
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,880
Aside from all the other things
I don't understand.

161
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:09,960
What does it matter?
Sooner or later, someone will come along

162
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:11,040
and rescue us.

163
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,040
Or enslave us.

164
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:15,000
First, we find the Tardis.

165
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:17,920
Quick thing before we go, if you feel
drawn to a particular room,

166
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,560
do not go in and make sure someone else
can see you at all times.

167
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:24,120
Joe said, "He will feast."

168
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,880
Is there something here with us?

169
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,720
(JOE LAUGHING)

170
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:31,480
Something to add, Joe?

171
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:33,920
"Here comes a candle
to light you to bed

172
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,920
"Here comes a chopper
to chop off your head

173
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,320
"Chop chop chop chop.”

174
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:41,240
Can we do something about him?

175
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:48,960
Personally, I think
you've got the right idea.

176
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:51,840
At times like this
I think of my old school motto,

177
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,480
"Resistance is exhausting”.

178
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,280
I've worked out where we are.

179
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:58,880
-Hmm?
-Norway!

180
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,600
-Norway?
-See, the US government

181
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:05,320
has entire cities hidden
in the Norwegian mountains.

182
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:09,160
See, Earth is on a collision course
with this other planet.

183
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:12,040
And this is where they're going to send
all the rich people when it kicks off.

184
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:14,320
-Amazing.
-It's all there on the internet.

185
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:16,880
No, it's amazing you've come up
with a theory even more insane

186
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,080
than what's actually happening.

187
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:21,040
(SCHOOL BELL RINGING)

188
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:22,760
Hello.

189
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:26,080
You've forgotten your PE kit again?

190
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:30,400
Right, that's it.
You're doing it in your pants.

191
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,840
(DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

192
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:35,920
Hey, don't...

193
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,720
(ALL CHATTING AND GIGGLING)

194
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:44,400
Oh look, girls. It's H-H-Howie!

195
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:45,600
(ALL GIGGLING)

196
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:48,560
(SCREAMING AND LAUGHING)

197
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,560
What's loser in K-K-K-Klingon?

198
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:53,720
-(STUTTERING)
-MALE VOICE: Praise him.

199
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,720
Shut the-the-the door!

200
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:04,760
This is just some messed-up CIA stuff.
I'm telling you...

201
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:08,680
You're right. Keep telling yourself
that. It's a CIA thing. Nothing more.

202
00:11:10,280 --> 00:11:11,360
(GROWLING)

203
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:49,120
Uh, guys...

204
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,120
Look.

205
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:53,280
(MONSTER GROWLING FIERCELY)

206
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,240
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

207
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:58,040
Well, whatever that is,
it's not real, yeah?

208
00:11:58,120 --> 00:12:01,160
No, no. I'm sure it isn't. But just in
case, let's run away and hide anyway.

209
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,240
In there!

210
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:04,080
No, this way!

211
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:05,400
I found a...

212
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:14,760
A B in Mathematics?

213
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:15,840
You are lazy.

214
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:18,800
Do you understand me, girl? Lazy.

215
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:22,280
I'm sorry. Daddy, I'm so sorry.

216
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:24,600
-(SCREAMING AND LAUGHING)
-(FEMALE VOICE) Praise him.

217
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:27,280
-Rory, come on! Come on!
-It was a...

218
00:12:30,760 --> 00:12:32,400
(EXCLAIMS)

219
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:34,680
Don't blink.

220
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:35,920
What?

221
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:43,760
DOCTOR: Amy, get back!

222
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:49,720
Why haven't they got us yet?

223
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:56,320
-Amy, they're not real.
-What?

224
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,800
They should have got us by now.

225
00:12:57,880 --> 00:13:01,840
Amy, look at me. Focus on me.
It's your bad dream, that's all.

226
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:07,760
-I don't even think they're for us.
-(THUDDING FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

227
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:09,080
(MONSTER ROARING)

228
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:10,160
Hide!

229
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,120
(MONSTER GROWLING)

230
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:15,880
Doctor, what are you doing?

231
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:19,400
It's all right, I just have to see what
it is. I've just, I have to see.

232
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:27,680
(GROWLING, FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

233
00:13:27,760 --> 00:13:30,240
Oh, look at you!

234
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:31,840
You are beautiful.

235
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,120
(MONSTER GROWLING)

236
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:39,520
Oh, dear.

237
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:54,400
I think it's going after joe.

238
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:56,520
Come on, come to me. Come to me.

239
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:57,920
(SCREAMING AND LAUGHING)

240
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,000
Praise him.

241
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:11,080
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

242
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,600
(GROWLING)

243
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:14,840
Leave him alone!

244
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:21,480
Joe!

245
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,320
Joe!

246
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:36,640
Joe!

247
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:45,960
Joe?

248
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:48,040
Joe!

249
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,160
Joe!

250
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:51,800
Joe, what happened?

251
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,040
(MONSTER GROWLING)

252
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,960
(KETTLE WHISTLING)

253
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:09,120
(ELECTRONIC BUZZING)

254
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:14,120
HOWIE: If we can wedge a chair
under the doorknob,

255
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:15,800
that should stop anything
from getting in.

256
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:18,400
RITA: Help yourself to tea.

257
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:21,760
Guys, tea over here.

258
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:25,680
If it's any consolation,
I've met the Weeping Angels.

259
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:29,960
So I know how...
In fact, I thought that room was for me.

260
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:32,360
Joe was right.

261
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:37,080
Whatever it is in here,
it actually wants to kill us.

262
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:40,120
Not oppress us or enslave us, kill us!

263
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:42,600
Listen,

264
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:47,320
the Doctor's been part of
my life for so long now

265
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:48,800
and he's never let me down.

266
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:53,840
Even when I thought he had when
I was a...a kid and he left me,

267
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:55,400
he came back.

268
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:57,960
He saved me. (LAUGHS)

269
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:02,200
And now he's going to save you.

270
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:08,440
But don't tell him I said that because
the smugness would be terrifying.

271
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:16,200
Of course, if the Weeping Angels
were meant for me,

272
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:18,040
then your room is still out there,

273
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:20,440
somewhere.

274
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:27,600
Every time the Doctor gets pally with
someone, I have this overwhelming urge

275
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:29,640
to notify their next of kin.

276
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:31,560
(STARTLED REACTION)

277
00:16:32,120 --> 00:16:36,640
Sorry, last time I said something
like that, you hit me with your shoe.

278
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,720
I think you literally had to sit down
and unlace it first.

279
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:41,040
(LAUGHING)

280
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,520
What exactly happened to him?

281
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:44,600
He died.

282
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:47,680
You are a medical doctor, aren't you?

283
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:50,880
You haven't just got a degree in
cheese-making or something...

284
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:54,080
No. Well, yes. Both, actually.
I mean, there is no cause.

285
00:16:54,160 --> 00:16:56,480
All his vital organs simply stopped

286
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:58,600
as if the simple spark of life,
his loves and hates,

287
00:16:58,680 --> 00:17:00,880
his faiths and fears were just...

288
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:03,240
(SNIFFING) ...taken.
And this is a cup of tea.

289
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:06,920
Of course, I'm British.
It's how we cope with trauma.

290
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,960
-Oh.
-That and tutting.

291
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:10,080
But how did you make it?

292
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:14,840
All hotels should have a well-stocked
kitchen. Even alien fake ones.

293
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:18,760
I heard you talking when you arrived.

294
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:23,200
Look, it's no more ridiculous
than Howie's CIA theory or mine.

295
00:17:23,320 --> 00:17:24,400
Which is?

296
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:25,920
This is Jahannam.

297
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,000
You're a Muslim!

298
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:29,640
Don't be frightened.

299
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:32,280
You think this is Hell?

300
00:17:33,920 --> 00:17:36,720
The whole '80s hotel thing
took me by surprise, though.

301
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:39,640
Ah. And all these fears and phobias

302
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:41,280
wandering about, most are
completely unconnected to us.

303
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:43,480
So why are they still here?

304
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:46,720
(SIGHS) Maybe the cleaners have
gone on strike?

305
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:47,920
(CHUCKLES)

306
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:52,400
I like you, you're a right clever clogs.
But this isn't Hell, Rita.

307
00:17:52,480 --> 00:17:55,120
You don't understand.
I say that without fear.

308
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:58,520
Jahannam will play its tricks and there
will be times I want to run and scream,

309
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:02,720
but I've tried to live a good life
and that knowledge keeps me sane,

310
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:06,120
despite the monsters
and the bonkers rooms.

311
00:18:06,280 --> 00:18:07,280
- (GARGLES)
-Gibbis...

312
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:11,160
-is an alien, isn't he?
-Yeah.

313
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:14,640
-Sorry.
-Okay. I'm going to file that under

314
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:17,920
-"freak out about later".
-AMY: Doctor, look at this.

315
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:22,440
I found it in a corridor.
I completely forgot I had it.

316
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:33,960
"My name is Lucy Hayward
and I'm the last one left.

317
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:37,760
"It took Luke first.

318
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:40,760
"It got him on his first day,
almost as soon as we arrived."

319
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:46,840
"You don't know what's going
to be in your room until you see it.

320
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:50,480
"Then you realise it could never
have been anything else.

321
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:54,960
"I just saw mine, it was a gorilla
from a book I'd read as a kid.

322
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:58,640
"My God, that thing used to terrify me.

323
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:02,880
"The gaps between my worships
are getting shorter, like contractions.

324
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:06,520
"This is what happened to the others.

325
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,520
"And how lucky they were.

326
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:12,760
"It's all so clear now.

327
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,760
"I'm so happy.”

328
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:18,920
-LUCY: Praise him.
-"Praise him."

329
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:20,360
Praise him.

330
00:19:21,520 --> 00:19:22,560
What did you just say?

331
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:25,040
Nothing.

332
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:29,760
-Praise him!
-This is what happened to Joe.

333
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,080
Oh, God. It's going to come for me now.

334
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:34,960
-No, it won't.
-(ALL SPEAKING AT ONCE)

335
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:37,080
I won't leave you. I promise.
You have my word on it.

336
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:39,240
-I don't want to get eaten.
-AMY: Howie, calm down.

337
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:42,440
He's gonna lead the monster right here!

338
00:19:42,520 --> 00:19:46,160
-Howie!
-(LOUD WHIRRING)

339
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:47,560
Don't you see?
You'll lead him right here.

340
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:48,920
What do you suggest?

341
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,960
Look, whatever it is out there,

342
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:54,680
it's obviously chosen Howard
as its next course.

343
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:59,320
Now, tragic though that is,
this is no time for sentiment.

344
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:03,080
I'm saying if it were to find him,

345
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:05,880
it may be satisfied
and let the rest of us go.

346
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:10,400
(SIGHS) AILI want to do is go home
and be conquered and oppressed.

347
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:11,760
Is that too much to ask?

348
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:14,520
It's okay. I'll stay with Howie.
You take the others and go.

349
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:16,400
No. We stay together.

350
00:20:22,520 --> 00:20:25,520
Your civilisation is
one of the oldest in the galaxy.

351
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:28,120
Now I see why.

352
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:33,600
Your cowardice isn't quaint,
it's sly, aggressive.

353
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:36,920
It's how that dune of gutlessness
has survived

354
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:39,160
while so many others have perished.

355
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:42,040
Well, not today.

356
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:45,880
No one else dies today.

357
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,280
Right?

358
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:50,040
(MUTTERING)

359
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:52,880
Brilliant.

360
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:57,640
Howie, any second now,
it's going to possess you again.

361
00:20:57,800 --> 00:21:01,840
When it does, I'm going to ask you some
questions. Please try to answer them.

362
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:07,040
I hope my mum's all right.
She's going to be worried.

363
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:09,160
DOCTOR: Howie?

364
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:12,280
Howie.

365
00:21:13,760 --> 00:21:15,840
Howie, you're next.
We're all dead jealous.

366
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:18,360
So, tell us,
how do we get a piece of the action?

367
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:20,560
-(CHUCKLES)
-Why isn't he possessing all of us?

368
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:23,520
You guys have got
all these distractions.

369
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,160
All these obstacles.

370
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:30,360
It'll be so much easier if you just
let it go, you know? Clear the path.

371
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:33,760
You want it to find you, even though
you know what it's going to do?

372
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,880
Are you kidding?

373
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:39,360
He's going to kill us all.
How cool is that?

374
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:47,440
It's as I thought. It feeds on fear.

375
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:49,600
Everything. The rooms, Lucy's note.

376
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:53,640
I mean, even the pictures in reception
have been put here to frighten us.

377
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:56,200
So we have to resist it.
Do whatever you have to.

378
00:21:56,280 --> 00:21:58,720
Cross your fingers. Say a prayer.
Think of a basket of kittens.

379
00:21:58,800 --> 00:22:01,360
But do not give in to the fear.

380
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:04,840
Okay, but what are we
actually going to do?

381
00:22:06,280 --> 00:22:08,880
We're going to catch ourselves
a monster.

382
00:22:12,120 --> 00:22:13,720
HOWIE: Bring me death.

383
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:16,080
Bring me glory!

384
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:19,520
My master, my lord, I'm here.

385
00:22:20,560 --> 00:22:23,120
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

386
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:26,840
Come to me.

387
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:31,000
I'm waiting, here, for you.

388
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:34,800
He has promised me a glorious death.

389
00:22:40,560 --> 00:22:45,080
Give it to me now.
I want him to know my devotion.

390
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:54,720
Is he to do with you?

391
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:57,680
-AMY: How's it going?
-Don't talk to the clown.

392
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:04,080
HOWIE: Praise him.

393
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:10,240
Praise him.

394
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:13,280
Rory, he's in!

395
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:22,840
HOWIE: Let his name
be the last thing I hear.

396
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:28,160
Let his breath on my skin
be the last thing I feel.

397
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:34,080
I was lost in the shadows
but he found me.

398
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:40,400
His love was a beacon
that led me from darkness to light

399
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:45,040
and now I am blinded by his majesty.

400
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:49,000
Humbled by his glory!

401
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:52,840
-Praise him.
-That's quite enough of that.

402
00:23:53,320 --> 00:23:54,680
(FEEDBACK SCREECHING)

403
00:23:57,040 --> 00:23:58,360
What's going on?

404
00:24:00,160 --> 00:24:01,160
You lied to me.

405
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:03,480
Calm down, Howie.
This is for your own good.

406
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,800
At least stand where I can see you.

407
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:08,560
I've been told not to speak to you.

408
00:24:09,320 --> 00:24:10,880
It don't mean you can't listen.

409
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:12,520
Nothing personal.

410
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:14,640
(GROWLING)

411
00:24:14,720 --> 00:24:16,800
I just think
we should take things slow.

412
00:24:18,160 --> 00:24:19,280
Get to know each other.

413
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:21,720
(ROARING)

414
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:26,080
You take people's most primal fears
and pop it in a room.

415
00:24:26,760 --> 00:24:29,080
Tailor-made hell just for them. Why?

416
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:30,680
(GROWLING)

417
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:33,280
Did you say "they take"?

418
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:34,960
(GROANS)

419
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:38,880
Ah, what is that word? The...guard?

420
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:42,200
No, the...the warden.

421
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,160
This is a prison.

422
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:48,480
You were right, you know.

423
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:51,440
Chances are, if you hand me over,
he'll leave you alone.

424
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:55,440
Yeah, but we saw how that idea
got shot down in flames.

425
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:58,640
It's not like kicking me out of a plane
to lighten the load.

426
00:24:58,720 --> 00:25:00,840
I'm asking you for this.
I'm begging you.

427
00:25:01,080 --> 00:25:03,120
You're possessed. You'd say anything.

428
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:05,600
Possessed guys can be quite strong.

429
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:09,720
Who's to say I didn't overpower you?

430
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:14,320
DOCTOR: So what are we? Cellmates?

431
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:16,040
Lunch?

432
00:25:16,120 --> 00:25:17,200
(GROWLING)

433
00:25:17,880 --> 00:25:21,760
We are not ripe.

434
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,680
This is what Joe said,
that we weren't ready.

435
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:34,920
So, what? What? You make us ready?

436
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:37,040
You, what? Replace?

437
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:39,880
Replace what? Fear?

438
00:25:42,800 --> 00:25:48,320
You have lived so long,
even your name is lost.

439
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:56,320
You want this to stop.

440
00:25:57,920 --> 00:26:02,760
Because you are just instinct.

441
00:26:03,120 --> 00:26:04,360
(GROWLING)

442
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:07,920
Then tell me. Tell me how to fight you.

443
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:13,080
HOWIE: My master, my lord. I'm here!

444
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:15,360
-That's Howie.
-He's got out.

445
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:17,920
Oh! Bring me death.

446
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:19,320
No, no, no, no!

447
00:26:21,240 --> 00:26:22,640
Rory, watch out!

448
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:24,600
(EXCLAIMS)

449
00:26:24,680 --> 00:26:25,720
Stay back!

450
00:26:28,280 --> 00:26:29,760
Pond, bring the fish.

451
00:26:29,840 --> 00:26:32,360
The fish? Oh, the fish.

452
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:35,000
-Where'd he go?
-Somebody hit me.

453
00:26:35,080 --> 00:26:36,760
Was it Amy? (LAUGHS)

454
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:52,560
Rory, you all right?

455
00:26:55,560 --> 00:26:57,200
We should find the Doctor.

456
00:27:15,760 --> 00:27:17,080
VOICES: (WHISPERING) Praise him.

457
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:19,440
Praise him. Praise him.

458
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:21,640
You shouldn't have done that.

459
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:23,560
-What did you see?
-Nothing.

460
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:25,720
-Nothing. I don't know. It was weird.
-Come on.

461
00:28:09,360 --> 00:28:12,600
He got free. He overpowered me.

462
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:20,720
It might leave us alone now.

463
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,160
Maybe now we'll be safe.

464
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:25,480
Wait!

465
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:35,440
Have you found your room yet?

466
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:37,560
No.

467
00:28:39,360 --> 00:28:40,920
Is that good or bad?

468
00:28:42,040 --> 00:28:43,720
Maybe you're not scared of anything.

469
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:47,280
Well, after all the time I spent
with you in the Tardis,

470
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:48,920
what was left to be scared of?

471
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:52,560
You said that in the past tense.

472
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,640
No, I didn't.

473
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:00,600
You know,
Howie had been in speech therapy.

474
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:02,640
He'd just got over this massive stammer.

475
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:08,120
What an achievement.
I mean, can you imagine?

476
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:12,280
I'd forgotten not all victories
are about saving the universe.

477
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:24,680
Rita! Brilliant!

478
00:29:25,320 --> 00:29:27,680
How are you? Not panicking, are you?

479
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:29,800
Good, good.

480
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:33,560
Because I'm literally an otter's toenail
away from getting us out of here.

481
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:35,920
-Why?
-Excellent question.

482
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:37,800
Excellent question.

483
00:29:38,680 --> 00:29:40,120
Why what?

484
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:41,680
Why is up to you to save us?

485
00:29:41,760 --> 00:29:44,560
That's quite a God complex
you have there.

486
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:49,360
DOCTOR: I brought them here.

487
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:51,560
They'd say it was their choice,

488
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:54,800
but offer a child a suitcase
full of sweets and they'll take it.

489
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:58,600
Offer someone all of time and space
and they'll take that, too.

490
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:03,560
Which is why you shouldn't.

491
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:05,800
Which is why grown-ups were invented.

492
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:09,120
-All of time and space, eh?
-Oh, yeah.

493
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:11,720
And when we get out of this,
I'll show you, too.

494
00:30:11,800 --> 00:30:14,080
I don't know what you're talking about,
but whatever it was,

495
00:30:14,160 --> 00:30:16,200
-I have a feeling you just did it again.
-(CHUCKLES)

496
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:21,600
Right down to the smallest detail.

497
00:30:21,680 --> 00:30:23,040
Got you, Mr Minotaur.

498
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:34,400
Praise him.

499
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:44,320
VOICES: (ECHOING) Praise him.
Praise him. Praise him.

500
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:47,120
(ECHOING CONTINUES)

501
00:31:08,320 --> 00:31:09,560
Of course.

502
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,680
Who else?

503
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:36,760
Oh, you beauty! Come on, big fella.
Where are you?

504
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:40,320
Ah. Ahh...

505
00:31:43,760 --> 00:31:44,800
Rita, where are you going?

506
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:49,200
(PHONE RINGING)

507
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:54,040
Come on, come on, come on.

508
00:32:00,080 --> 00:32:01,080
Come on.

509
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:02,600
(PHONE PICKS UP)

510
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:04,760
Rita, where are you going?

511
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:07,520
Can you take the phone
into the corridor? Will it reach?

512
00:32:11,360 --> 00:32:12,800
You started to praise it, didn't you?

513
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:18,560
Rita, come back, please.

514
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:20,920
We'll find a way to stop it,
I swear to you.

515
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:23,240
No, I need to get as far away
from you all as possible.

516
00:32:23,320 --> 00:32:25,960
No, no, no, you don't. The creature
only wants whoever's praising it.

517
00:32:26,040 --> 00:32:27,520
And then you'll put yourself in its way.

518
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:31,320
I'm coming to get you. Block out the
fear and stay focused on your belief.

519
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:34,640
The hotel will keep us apart.
I could be 50 miles away by now.

520
00:32:34,760 --> 00:32:36,200
(FAINT GROWLING)

521
00:32:36,280 --> 00:32:38,960
I want you to do me
one last favour, Doctor.

522
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:42,680
I can feel the rapture approaching
like a wave.

523
00:32:44,040 --> 00:32:47,640
I don't want you to witness this.
I want you to remember me the way I was.

524
00:32:48,320 --> 00:32:49,720
(ROARING)

525
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:53,800
What's going on? Rita's disappeared.

526
00:32:53,880 --> 00:32:55,400
What is she doing there?

527
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:56,840
Rita.

528
00:32:57,400 --> 00:32:59,240
Rita, please.

529
00:32:59,480 --> 00:33:01,000
Let me find you.

530
00:33:01,280 --> 00:33:03,560
You stay where you are.

531
00:33:03,640 --> 00:33:05,960
Please, let me be robbed of my faith
in private.

532
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:09,440
Look, Rita, Rita, go into the room.
Lock the door.

533
00:33:09,520 --> 00:33:12,240
I'm not frightened. I'm blessed, Doctor.

534
00:33:12,480 --> 00:33:13,880
(GROWLING)

535
00:33:13,960 --> 00:33:15,200
I'm at peace.

536
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:19,320
-I'm going to hang up.
-No, no, no, Rita.

537
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:21,160
-Goodbye, Doctor.
-Rita!

538
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:24,000
-Thank you for trying.
-Rita, please! Please!

539
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:26,600
Please!

540
00:33:26,840 --> 00:33:28,200
(ROARING)

541
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:55,880
(WHIRRING)

542
00:34:11,640 --> 00:34:13,040
(CRASHING)

543
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:14,880
(YELLING)

544
00:34:24,280 --> 00:34:25,440
Okay.

545
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:29,640
He preys on people's fear
and possesses them.

546
00:34:30,160 --> 00:34:33,200
But Rita wasn't afraid.
She was brave and calm.

547
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:36,480
Maybe it's something to do
with the people,

548
00:34:36,560 --> 00:34:39,160
some connection between the four of you
that will tell me how to fight it.

549
00:34:39,240 --> 00:34:42,000
Yes, you keep saying that,
but you never do.

550
00:34:42,200 --> 00:34:44,760
And while we wait, people keep dying,
and we'll be next!

551
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:46,280
Look, he'll work it out, he always does.

552
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:49,320
Just let him riff and move
anything expensive out of his way.

553
00:34:51,080 --> 00:34:52,280
Oh, no.

554
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:55,720
-Oh, no, no...
-Doctor, what is wrong?

555
00:34:56,160 --> 00:34:57,600
It's not fear.

556
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:01,520
It's faith.

557
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:04,800
Not just religious faith.
Faith in something.

558
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:08,400
Howard believed in conspiracies, that
external forces controlled the world.

559
00:35:08,480 --> 00:35:11,360
Joe had dice cuff links and a chain
with a horseshoe. He was a gambler.

560
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:14,720
Gamblers believe in luck, an intangible
force that helps them win or lose.

561
00:35:14,840 --> 00:35:17,120
Gibbis has rejected
any personal autonomy, and he's waiting

562
00:35:17,200 --> 00:35:20,200
for the next batch of invaders
to oppress him and tell him what to do.

563
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:23,200
They all believe there's something
guiding them, about to save them.

564
00:35:23,720 --> 00:35:24,880
That's what it replaces.

565
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:27,480
Every time someone was confronted
with their most primal fear,

566
00:35:27,560 --> 00:35:30,400
they fell back on
their most fundamental faith.

567
00:35:32,640 --> 00:35:35,880
And all this time,
I have been telling you to dig deep,

568
00:35:37,560 --> 00:35:39,640
find the thing that keeps you brave.

569
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:43,000
I made you expose your faith.

570
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:46,600
Showed them what they needed.

571
00:35:47,480 --> 00:35:50,040
But why us? Why are we here?

572
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:52,560
It doesn't want you. That's why
it kept showing you a way out.

573
00:35:52,640 --> 00:35:54,000
You're not religious or superstitious,

574
00:35:54,080 --> 00:35:56,440
so there's no faith
for you to fall back on.

575
00:35:58,800 --> 00:36:00,360
It wants her.

576
00:36:00,560 --> 00:36:01,640
Me?

577
00:36:09,680 --> 00:36:12,360
-Why?
-Your faith in me.

578
00:36:16,120 --> 00:36:17,840
That's what brought us here.

579
00:36:24,560 --> 00:36:26,560
But why do they lose their faith
before they die?

580
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:30,160
And start worshipping...it?

581
00:36:30,680 --> 00:36:33,560
It needs to convert the faith
into a form it can consume.

582
00:36:33,680 --> 00:36:34,800
Faith is an energy,

583
00:36:34,880 --> 00:36:37,920
the specific emotional energy
the creature needs to live.

584
00:36:38,160 --> 00:36:40,280
Which is why, at the end of her note,
Lucy said...

585
00:36:40,360 --> 00:36:41,680
-AMY: "Praise him."
-Exactly.

586
00:36:49,800 --> 00:36:50,960
No.

587
00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:53,400
Oh, please, no.

588
00:36:53,600 --> 00:36:54,920
(FOOTSTEPS POUNDING)

589
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,360
(GROWLING)

590
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:14,320
Amy!

591
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:17,720
-What are you doing?
-Oh, he's beautiful.

592
00:37:17,800 --> 00:37:19,280
GIBBIS: Leave her. Just leave her!

593
00:37:30,600 --> 00:37:31,920
(GROWLING)

594
00:37:34,720 --> 00:37:39,040
Doctor, it's happening. It's changing
me. It's changing my thoughts.

595
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:42,560
I can't save you from this.
There's nothing I can do to stop this.

596
00:37:43,120 --> 00:37:44,600
-What?
-I stole your childhood

597
00:37:44,680 --> 00:37:47,320
and now I've led you by the hand
to your death.

598
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:49,160
But the worst thing is, I knew.

599
00:37:49,360 --> 00:37:52,280
I knew this would happen.
This is what always happens.

600
00:38:01,920 --> 00:38:03,360
Forget your faith in me.

601
00:38:08,920 --> 00:38:10,240
(BELLOWS)

602
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:16,360
I took you with me because I was vain.

603
00:38:17,720 --> 00:38:19,760
Because I wanted to be adored.

604
00:38:23,040 --> 00:38:24,120
Look at you.

605
00:38:26,360 --> 00:38:28,280
The glorious Pond,

606
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:31,200
the girl who waited for me.

607
00:38:37,680 --> 00:38:39,040
I'm not a hero.

608
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:43,840
I really am just a madman in a box.

609
00:38:45,800 --> 00:38:48,400
And it's time we saw each other
as we really are.

610
00:39:04,360 --> 00:39:06,040
Amy Williams...

611
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:14,240
it's time to stop waiting.

612
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:29,920
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDING)

613
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:33,760
(MONSTER BREATHING HEAVILY)

614
00:39:59,840 --> 00:40:01,720
I severed the food supply,

615
00:40:02,520 --> 00:40:04,400
sacrificing their faith in me.

616
00:40:06,600 --> 00:40:08,280
Gave you the space to die.

617
00:40:09,040 --> 00:40:10,200
(SHUSHING)

618
00:40:31,720 --> 00:40:34,600
What is it? A minotaur or an alien?

619
00:40:34,920 --> 00:40:36,360
Or an alien minotaur?

620
00:40:37,240 --> 00:40:39,280
That's not a question
I thought I'd be asking this morning.

621
00:40:39,360 --> 00:40:42,080
I mean, it's both, actually.
Yeah. Here we go.

622
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:45,400
A distant cousin of the Nimon.

623
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:49,000
They descend on planets and set
themselves up as gods to be worshipped,

624
00:40:49,520 --> 00:40:52,440
which is fine until the inhabitants
get all secular

625
00:40:52,520 --> 00:40:55,160
and advanced enough
to build bunkers, prisons.

626
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:56,640
RORY: Correction.

627
00:40:57,920 --> 00:41:00,280
-Prisons in space.
-AMY: Where are the guards?

628
00:41:00,360 --> 00:41:03,160
No need for any. It's all automated.
It drifts through space,

629
00:41:04,120 --> 00:41:05,600
snatching people with belief systems,

630
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:07,920
and converts their faith into food
for the creature.

631
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:10,200
See that planet there?

632
00:41:10,880 --> 00:41:12,840
-Which one?
-The grey one, there.

633
00:41:12,920 --> 00:41:14,520
-Mmm-hmm.
-That's where I'm from.

634
00:41:14,640 --> 00:41:16,160
It didn't want just me.

635
00:41:16,240 --> 00:41:18,880
So, you must believe in some god
or someone

636
00:41:18,960 --> 00:41:20,800
or they'd have shown you the door, too.

637
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:24,120
So what do Time Lords pray to?

638
00:41:25,800 --> 00:41:29,600
According to the in-flight recorder,
the programme developed glitches.

639
00:41:30,280 --> 00:41:32,400
Got stuck on the same setting.

640
00:41:32,960 --> 00:41:35,520
The fears from the people before us
weren't tidied away.

641
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:37,840
(GROANING SOFTLY)

642
00:41:39,640 --> 00:41:41,040
AMY: What's it saying?

643
00:41:41,160 --> 00:41:45,320
"An ancient creature,
drenched in the blood

644
00:41:46,360 --> 00:41:48,160
"of the innocent.

645
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:52,840
"Drifting in space
through an endless shifting maze.

646
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:55,080
"For such a creature,

647
00:41:57,040 --> 00:41:59,160
"death would be a gift."

648
00:42:03,760 --> 00:42:05,160
Then, accept it.

649
00:42:07,360 --> 00:42:08,680
And sleep well.

650
00:42:12,320 --> 00:42:13,640
(GROWLING)

651
00:42:13,720 --> 00:42:16,440
"I wasn't talking about myself."

652
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:28,680
GIBBIS: Could I have a lift?

653
00:42:29,800 --> 00:42:31,880
Just to the nearest galaxy will do.

654
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:43,200
(WHOOSHING)

655
00:42:52,600 --> 00:42:54,840
Don't tell me. This isn't Earth.
That isn't a real house.

656
00:42:54,920 --> 00:42:57,560
Inside lives a goblin
who feeds on indecision.

657
00:42:57,640 --> 00:43:01,680
Nope. Real Earth. Real house.
Real door keys.

658
00:43:02,800 --> 00:43:04,520
-You're not serious.
-The car, too?

659
00:43:05,120 --> 00:43:07,680
That...that's my favourite car.

660
00:43:07,760 --> 00:43:09,120
How did you know
that was my favourite car?

661
00:43:09,200 --> 00:43:11,880
You showed me a picture of it once
and said, "That's my favourite car."

662
00:43:11,960 --> 00:43:13,160
(BOTH LAUGHING)

663
00:43:13,240 --> 00:43:15,760
Rory, can you give us two minutes?

664
00:43:15,840 --> 00:43:17,840
Two minutes.

665
00:43:17,920 --> 00:43:20,360
She'll say that we can't accept it
because it's too extravagant

666
00:43:20,440 --> 00:43:22,440
and we'll always feel
a crippling sense of obligation.

667
00:43:24,800 --> 00:43:27,800
It's a risk I'm willing to take.

668
00:43:31,560 --> 00:43:32,680
Hey.

669
00:43:36,280 --> 00:43:37,320
So...

670
00:43:39,040 --> 00:43:40,800
You're leaving, aren't you?

671
00:43:42,040 --> 00:43:43,840
You haven't seen the last of me.

672
00:43:43,920 --> 00:43:46,960
Bad Penny is my middle name.

673
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:50,520
Seriously, the looks I get
when I fill in a form, it's...

674
00:43:51,400 --> 00:43:52,520
Why now?

675
00:43:55,960 --> 00:43:58,520
Because you're still breathing.

676
00:44:03,560 --> 00:44:06,040
Well, I think
this is about the washing up.

677
00:44:10,040 --> 00:44:13,200
Oh, you're right. There's still
heaps of stuff out there to look at.

678
00:44:13,280 --> 00:44:14,960
Do you know, there's a planet

679
00:44:15,200 --> 00:44:18,760
whose name literally translates
as "Volatile Sadness"?

680
00:44:23,400 --> 00:44:27,000
Or maybe there's a bigger, scarier
adventure waiting for you in there.

681
00:44:32,280 --> 00:44:35,560
Even so, it can't happen like this.

682
00:44:36,040 --> 00:44:37,960
After everything we've been through,
Doctor,

683
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:40,360
everything,

684
00:44:41,480 --> 00:44:45,800
you can't just drop me off at my house
and say goodbye like we've shared a cab.

685
00:44:48,080 --> 00:44:51,120
And what's the alternative?
Me standing over your grave?

686
00:44:52,440 --> 00:44:55,800
Over your broken body? Over Rory's body?

687
00:45:21,080 --> 00:45:24,840
If you bump into my daughter,
tell her to visit her old mum sometime.

688
00:45:27,520 --> 00:45:28,800
Look after him.

689
00:45:30,560 --> 00:45:31,600
Look after you.

690
00:45:57,360 --> 00:45:59,040
Bye.

691
00:46:03,600 --> 00:46:04,600
Bye.

692
00:46:04,840 --> 00:46:06,880
(WHOOSHING)

693
00:46:13,240 --> 00:46:15,040
What happened?

694
00:46:16,400 --> 00:46:18,360
What's he doing?

695
00:46:24,680 --> 00:46:26,680
He's saving us.

696
00:47:05,440 --> 00:47:07,280
Hello, Craig. I'm back.

697
00:47:07,480 --> 00:47:10,360
-What are you here for?
-I'm the Doctor. I work in a shop now.

698
00:47:10,520 --> 00:47:12,480
OWENS: You noticed something
and you're investigating it,

699
00:47:12,560 --> 00:47:15,000
and because it's you,
it's going to be dangerous and alien.

700
00:47:15,280 --> 00:47:16,440
What is that?

701
00:47:16,920 --> 00:47:17,960
Help me!

702
00:47:19,040 --> 00:47:20,160
No!

703
00:47:20,560 --> 00:47:21,720
-Doctor!
-Craig!

704
00:47:24,160 --> 00:47:25,200
(SCREAMING)

